{"questionId":"13974899","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The computer then selects at random an integer <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn></math>, inclusive. Each outcome is equally likely.</p>\n<p>Daniel is trying to determine the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> and asks if <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>7</mn></math>. He is told that it is not <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>7</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find, in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>, the expected information gained when the coin is flipped once.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mfenced><mi>I</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>p</mi><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>p</mi><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>p</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>p</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[1 mark]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13974899","referenceCode":"23N.3.AHL.TZ0.2dii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find, in terms of p, the expected information gained when the coin is flipped once.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.7—Optimisation","Topic